title: Teen wounded in arm in south Kansas City shooting
content:
KANSAS CITY, MO (KCTV) -
Police are investigating a shooting after a teenager was shot in the arm.
It happened near a home located on East 91st Street and Wallace Avenue in south Kansas City.
That neighborhood is just east of James A. Reed Road and south of O'Hara High School.
The shooting happened around 8:30 p.m.
There is no immediate suspect information available.
